This is "imerge", Kernighan's & Pike's "idiff" program out of their
fabulous book "The UNIX Programming Environment" (Prentice-Hall 1984).
Check out more info about the book (and the entire software suite)
at http://cm.bell-labs.com/cm/cs/upe/ .

In short, imerge runs a diff on two files and asks interactively
for each delta which variant should go into a third, merged file.

I typed in the little C program directly from the book back in 1986
or some such.  I just noticed today (2000) that the entire code of
the book is now available through the Internet.  (It didn't float
around on Usenet back then.)  The copyright in the package says:

