In since I didn't apply significant changes to the code this still
is all which applies.  Have fun with it.

Not after hesitating for a some time, I took liberty to change the name
when I wrote program and man page.  I think "imerge" captures the
purpose of the tool so much better and I still think "man -k" should be
enough to save day.

Sooner or later, I took imerge/idiff with me wherever I had to do some
work, without changing anything much.  It's now  CVS'ed for easier
accessibility.

Use the repository :pserver:anoncvs@cvs.gaertner.de:/usr/local/cvs with
password "cvs" to check for any updates.   Which are unlikely, though.
These AT&T folks sure were able to avoid version numbers other than
"1.0".  And I'm not intending to break with this fine tradition where
not necessary.

						Martin Neitzel
